node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 13, 2021 tagging @johellaponte. May be an image of text that says 'Johell Aponte @JohellAponte 4 years ago, my marriage was at the brink of a divorce. My business got me $80K in debt. I was losing control over my life due to my bad habits. Here are 4 things that allowed me to turn my life around...'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 13, 2021 tagging @johellaponte. May be an image of text that says 'Johell Aponte @JohellAponte 1. Reinvent yourself To succeed, you need to change ENTIRELY as a person. Most people: -Don't sleep well -Don't have a routine -Don't learn about themselves You need to: -Build discipline -Create routines -Lean new information'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 13, 2021 tagging @johellaponte. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Johell Aponte @JohellAponte 2. Obsession This is something no one talks about. Being interested is not enough, you need to be obsessed with you goals. Once you're obsessed, you will find ways to achieve in a week for instance what would normally take you months.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 13, 2021 tagging @johellaponte. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Johell Aponte @JohellAponte 3. Sacrifice had to eave my old friends behind -I gave up my bad habits to grow had to stop playing it safe sacrificed my social life Sacrifice is a choice, and you make it when something is important enough to you.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 13, 2021 tagging @johellaponte. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Johell Aponte @JohellAponte 4. Discipline Motivation is a luxury that comes and goes, discipline sticks with you unti you say otherwise. You have to understand you cannot always be motivated, you have to be disciplined.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 13, 2021 tagging @johellaponte. Here's how we got to this point...'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of text that says 'JefS Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger I'll keep this short short and sweet. When was in college, addiction. had a bad I'll let you interpret what that means... I'm not proud of it, but it was caused by problems in my personal life that I've now learned a lot from.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of text that says 'Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger Fast forward a few years and was on and off with my addiction. had a corporate job at the biggest bank in America. And finally quit when was sitting in my cubicle as realized... "This isn't the life I want to live."'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of text that says 'Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger Corporate was hammering me for posting free finance content. The job also held me back from what truly wanted out of life, which was freedom and to truly help others, Not just to stack some billionaire's pockets. That's when quit my job and started my first business.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of text that says 'Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger It was a business centered around helping others with credit and funding. Our first month, we did $5k, then $10k, $25k, $50k, and it started blowing up. Now that business is doing millions in sales annually, and those helped needed a place to invest the extra money they made.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of text that says 'Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger Our clients always got great results on the credit side to get funding for businesses, investments, etc. They saw that I've invested my own money into crypto as early as 2012, so they wanted to get in on the opportunity. Since our launch, we've got $40M in the fund and growing.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of text that says 'Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger Did get lucky by stumbling on Bitcoin and crypto early? Yeah. Did turn a shitty situation with my addiction into a huge opportunity for me and others? Also, yeah.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger There are tons of lessons you can learn from my journey, but the most important one is recognizing good opportunities when you have them. It has allowed me to create multiple businesses just from solving the problems the people work with had.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 12, 2021 tagging @jeffsekinger. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'JefS Jeff Sekinger @jeffsekinger If you want to see more content around fixing your credit and investing in crypto, follow me. You won't be disappointed.'.
